    "Similarly, we can construct the normalized log closure amplitude χ 2 log CA as:",
    "ln A C is the number of log closure amplitude data points, ÂC is the model closure amplitude, A C is the real data closure amplitude, and σ 2 ln A C is the log closure amplitude standard deviation.",
    "Readers can refer to Sect. 2.1 of M 87 * 2017 IV for additional details about constructing normalized closure χ 2 A79, page 15 of 63 The Event Horizon Telescope Collaboration: A&A, 681, A79 (2024) values, which should not be confused for the formal definition of a reduced χ 2.",
    "In Table 5, we show the normalized χ 2 values for the fiducial images and normalized χ 2 statistics across the Top Sets for DIFMAP, eht-imaging, and SMILI.",
